Usually USER---->(request)--->RESOURCEand resource replies for the request.

But in this design pattern we introduce a "PROXY" in between User and Resource.
Proxy object acts as a placeholder to control access to the real object. The client communicates with the proxy, which forwards requests to the real object.

This helps to manage access to resource-intensive or sensitive objects without exposing 
internal details and allows adding responsibilties like security or logging 
without modifying the ral object.

USER-->PROXY-->RESOURCE
User doesnt know proxy replies to it.

1.VIRTUAL PROXY: protect an expensive resource through proxy by not allowing to cretae the object until the methods are called (in expensive resource).
  Because unecessary memeory is wasted. and no one is using that.

  Here application method(expensive resource method) gets slowed down a bit when called because of proxy but 
  it is a trade off better let it be bit late rather than using up unnecessary memory.

2.REMOTE PROXY:Remote proxy acts as local representative for object running on different machine, handling communication details like network calls.

3.SECURITY PROXY:These proxies can control access to sensitive resources by checking user permission before forwarding requests, commonly used in authentication and authorization systems.


Components:
1.SUBJECT:It is interface or an abstract class that defines the common interface shared by Real Subject and Proxy classes.
 It declares the methods that the proxy uses to control access to the RealSubject.
 Usually includes methods that client code can invoke on RealSubject and the proxy.

2.REALSUBJECT:It is the actual object that proxy represents.It contains real implementation of the business logic or resource that client code want ti access.

3.PROXY:It acts as surrogate for the RealSubject, It controls access to the real object and may provide addtional functionality such as "LAZY LOADING", "ACCESS CONTROL" or "LOGGING"
It implements the same interface as RealSubject (SUBJECT INTERFACE)
Maintains a reference to the RealSubject
Controls access to the RealSubject, adding addtional logic if necessary.



Working:
Cliet interacts with proxy instead of real object.
The proxy controls access to the real object  and may add extra behaviuir.
The real object is created or accessed only when required.
After processing, the proxy forwards the request to real object.


